CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 1, 1953, pg. 12, reads: "Annual Breakfast Is Gala - The gala annual breakfast given by the smart Min-Ceil Club on the lawn of the Emmett Davises of Lincoln Avenue, draw its usual socialite group of guests. Some snapped here include...Bottom photo: Louis Greene, Mr. and Mrs. Dudley Ellis of Brooklyn, M.Y.; Miss June Burr, Long Island, N.Y.; Mrs. Louise Jackson, Mrs. Ora G. Ware, Patricia Brown.  Standing: Mrs. Jayne Gantt and Mrs. Marilyn W. Brown...Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of guests of Min-Ceil Club, seated from left: Louis Greene, Dudley Ellis, Mrs. Ellis, June Burr, Louise Jackson, Ora G. Ware, Patricia Brown, and unknown girl; standing: Jayne Gantt and Marilyn W. Brown, gathered around table for gala annual breakfast, home of Mr. and Mrs. Emmett Davis, Lincoln Avenue
